• <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Refuse to take drug test or even answer any questions about drug use.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Not true. First, it should be noted that on a number of occasions George W. Bush has acknowledged he drank too much as a young adult. He has since quit drinking and from all reports, he is in excellent physical condition. Contrary to the claims of “the resume”, Mr. Bush did answer questions during the presidential campaign about rumors of past drug use. Bush denies using any illegal drug during the past 25 years (CNN) I’ll leave it up to you to determine whether a presidential candidate should submit to a drug test. <br>
